# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All major classes have multiple instances.
# - Resources are linked to ProductModels, Locations, Applications, and managed by Agents.
# - NetworkInterfaces are linked to Resources and NetworkLinks.
# - NetworkLinks are linked to Resources.
# - Applications are linked to ApplicationModules and Services.
# - ApplicationModules are linked to Applications and various Agent roles.
# - Services are linked to ApplicationModules.
# - EventRecords are linked to ManagedObjects (Resources/Applications), ManagementSystems (Applications), Agents, and trigger TroubleTickets.
# - TroubleTickets are linked to Services/Applications/Resources, Agents, EventRecords, and have Notes.
# - ChangeRequests are linked to Resources/Applications/Services, Agents, and have EventRecords in their history.
# - OperationPlans have Pre/Post Conditions.
# - AnomalyPatterns are linked to consequences and proposed repair actions (OperationPlans).
# - KOS concepts are used extensively.
# - rdfs:label and rdfs:comment are present.
# - No ldp prefix.
# - Token count should be substantial.

